Heraia is free software licensed under the GPLv2 or later. It is a standalone 
hexadecimal file analyser. It provides tools to analyse files in a hexadecimal 
way :
 
  . a data interpretor
  . a plugin that do some graphical analysis

It contains :

  . a fully functionnal plugin system
  . an extensible data interpretor 

It is written in C using GTK and based on GtkHex Widget. It is known to run on 
both Linux and Windows. It integrates smoothly with Gnome but it does not 
depends on it.

